{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Isa|30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","chapter":30,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":1,"text":"Woe to the rebellious children!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":2,"text":"Without asking my advice","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":3,"text":"But Pharaoh’s protection will become your shame,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":4,"text":"For though his princes are at Zoan","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":5,"text":"everyone will be ashamed","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":6,"text":"A pronouncement concerning the animals of the Negev:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":7,"text":"Egypt’s help is completely worthless;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":8,"text":"Go now, write it on a tablet in their presence","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":9,"text":"They are a rebellious people,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":10,"text":"They say to the seers, “Do not see,”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":11,"text":"Get out of the way!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":12,"text":"Therefore the Holy One of Israel says:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":13,"text":"this iniquity of yours will be","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":14,"text":"Its collapse will be like the shattering","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":15,"text":"For the Lord God, the Holy One of Israel, has said:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":16,"text":"You say, “No!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":17,"text":"One thousand will flee at the threat of one,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":18,"text":"Therefore the Lord is waiting to show you mercy,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":19,"text":"For people will live on Zion in Jerusalem. You will never weep again; he will show favor to you at the sound of your outcry; as soon as he hears, he will answer you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":20,"text":"The Lord will give you meager bread and water during oppression, but your Teacher will not hide any longer. Your eyes will see your Teacher,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":21,"text":"and whenever you turn to the right or to the left, your ears will hear this command behind you: “This is the way. Walk in it.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":22,"text":"Then you will defile your silver-plated idols and your gold-plated images. You will throw them away like menstrual cloths, and call them filth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":23,"text":"Then he will send rain for your seed that you have sown in the ground, and the food, the produce of the ground, will be rich and plentiful. On that day your cattle will graze in open pastures.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":24,"text":"The oxen and donkeys that work the ground will eat salted fodder scattered with winnowing shovel and fork.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":25,"text":"Streams flowing with water will be on every high mountain and every raised hill on the day of great slaughter when the towers fall.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":26,"text":"The moonlight will be as bright as the sunlight, and the sunlight will be seven times brighter —like the light of seven days —on the day that the Lord bandages his people’s injuries and heals the wounds he inflicted.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":27,"text":"Look! The name of the Lord is coming from far away,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":28,"text":"His breath is like an overflowing torrent","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":29,"text":"Your singing will be like that","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":30,"text":"And the Lord will make the splendor of his voice heard","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:31","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":31,"text":"Assyria will be shattered by the voice of the Lord.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:30:32","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Isa","bookOrder":22,"chapter":30,"verse":32,"text":"And every stroke of the appointed staff","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c